Chapter 12: They Don‚Äôt Like the Sun, Daytime Is Safe

The skinwalker‚Äôs presence had thrown my world into a frenzy, something I could not ignore. I had felt the air grow heavy with its malevolent energy, the shift in the very foundation of Mirror that had once been my sanctuary. As the days passed, I began to notice more‚Äîsmall details that only served to reinforce the creeping horror I now lived with.

