I didn‚Äôt know what the skinwalkers were doing‚Äîwhether they were lurking, waiting for a weakness to exploit, or whether they had already sensed the shift. But I felt confident. The LBRO had created a boundary that they couldn‚Äôt cross, no matter how well they could mimic. I had a sense of peace, but I knew that it was fleeting. In Mirror, peace was never permanent. Still, I had done what I could.

