I had thought the fight was over. I had been wrong. The skinwalkers had been waiting, adapting, learning. They weren‚Äôt just attacking‚Äîthey were infiltrating. They were no longer the brutish, obvious invaders I had battled before. They were subtle now, more dangerous than ever.

