And there, sitting at the center of it all, was the Skinwalker King.

He was unlike anything I had seen before. His form was tall, towering over me, and he was cloaked in shadows that moved like liquid. His face was obscured, not by a mask, but by the very fabric of the world itself, as if his presence was too immense for Mirror to contain. His eyes, however, were visible‚Äîtwo glowing orbs of pure darkness that seemed to burn with an inner fire. They locked onto me, and I could feel his gaze tearing through me, pulling at the very core of my being.

The Skinwalker King didn‚Äôt speak. He didn‚Äôt need to. His presence alone filled the cavern, like a heavy weight pressing against my chest. The air hummed with power, and I realized that this was the force I had been fighting all along. The skinwalkers were not just scavengers‚Äîthey were his children, his creations, his instruments of destruction.

He was their origin, their master.

And now, I was face-to-face with him.

Step 3: The King‚Äôs Silence

For a long time, neither of us moved. The cavern was silent except for the hum of the symbols on the walls, pulsing in a rhythmic pattern that seemed to resonate with the Skinwalker King‚Äôs presence.

I stood my ground, feeling the weight of his gaze pressing down on me. I knew that this was it. There was no escaping this moment. If I fought him, I would be facing the source of all the horrors I had encountered in Mirror. But I wasn‚Äôt going to back down. I had come too far, and Mirror had become my home. I wasn‚Äôt going to let this creature twist it into something unrecognizable.

