I waded into the water, my feet sinking into the cool depths. As I moved further in, the current grew stronger, pulling me in with a gentle but irresistible force. I didn‚Äôt fight it. I allowed myself to be carried, to follow the flow, trusting that it would lead me where I needed to go.

The water was deeper than I had imagined. The lake wasn‚Äôt just a shallow pool‚Äîit was vast, an endless expanse that stretched beneath the surface. As I ventured further into the depths, the light above began to fade, and the world around me grew darker, the water turning an inky black.

