The world above was fading, and as I sank deeper into the dark depths, I could feel the pull of the current becoming stronger, more intense. It was no longer a gentle flow‚Äîit was a whirlpool, spinning around me, drawing me toward its center.

I fought against it at first, instinctively trying to break free, but then I realized something: I wasn‚Äôt meant to fight it. The whirlpool was not a force to be resisted. It was a part of the world, a part of the flow. I had to learn to surrender to it, to let it carry me wherever it would.

I let go, allowing the current to take me deeper. The darkness around me enveloped me, but I felt no fear. There was only the pull of the water, the rhythm of the flow, and the realization that this‚Äîthis was the true essence of Mirror. Not the land, not the creatures, but the current. The flow of energy that connected everything in this world.

