Here, I would meditate. It wasn‚Äôt just about stillness. It was about connection. I would close my eyes, reach deep within myself, and listen to the world around me. The rustling of the leaves. The soft call of birds in the distance. The quiet hum of the earth, the subtle movements of the wind. Everything was a part of the same pulse, and I had learned to feel that pulse inside me. Meditation became a way to center myself, to understand my place in the grand web of life.

