I nodded, feeling a sense of peace settle within me. I had finally found a deeper connection with water‚Äînot as a force to be shaped, but as a partner in the dance of life. Just as the lobster and the crab had taught me, creation and destruction, chaos and order, weren‚Äôt opposites. They were two forces that existed together, as one.

