The Titan Lobster was easily the size of a mountain, its enormous claws snapping with the force of tidal waves. Its exoskeleton was made of iridescent shell armor, reflecting the sunlight in a brilliant array of colors, but it also had a harder, more metallic texture that made it nearly invulnerable to most attacks. The lobster‚Äôs body was lined with sharp, crystalline barbs, each one capable of cutting through rock and steel alike. Its antennae were long and moved with an almost sentient grace, sensing vibrations in the air and water from miles away.

