Chapter 73: Quiet Life in the City + Mira Returns Home

It had been a long journey‚Äîone filled with adventures, discoveries, and the deep unraveling of reality itself. The exploration of the Yarn Portals, the creation of permanent gateways, and the endless possibilities of the Magic Yarn had given me a sense of purpose, a sense of connection to the world I had come to inhabit. But after all the excitement, the challenges, and the revelations, I found myself longing for something simpler: a quiet life.

The city of New Mirror was vast, alive with possibility, yet I had never felt the need for constant movement, for always being in the thick of things. What I longed for now was peace. A stillness. A return to a rhythm that didn‚Äôt require portals, dimensions, or bending the very fabric of the world.
