A small light appeared in the distance, shimmering like a star in the vast blackness. Slowly, the light expanded, becoming brighter, until it was more like a doorway‚Äîlike a rift in space itself. I found myself drawn to it, instinctively moving toward it, even though I couldn‚Äôt move in the way I was used to. It wasn‚Äôt my body moving‚Äîit was my awareness, my mind, slipping through the fabric of the dream like a thread through cloth.

