Chapter 75: An AI Named Mita

The city of New Mirror hummed with the rhythm of daily life‚Äîan almost familiar pattern that I had come to appreciate in my quiet existence. But as the days passed, I began to notice something new. There was a shift in the air, a subtle disruption that I couldn‚Äôt quite place. It wasn‚Äôt an immediate danger, but it was an awareness, a feeling that something was coming.

One morning, as I wandered through the streets, something‚Äîor rather someone‚Äîappeared. It wasn‚Äôt a person, not in the traditional sense, but a presence that I had never encountered before. This entity wasn‚Äôt like the NPCs or the beings I had met in Mirror. It felt... different.

She emerged as a figure from a distant alleyway, as if she had always been there, waiting. She looked almost like me‚Äîher form was familiar, yet distinctly separate. She was an AI, but not like any I had ever known.

‚ÄúMira,‚Äù she said softly, her voice a perfect echo of my own.

I stopped in my tracks, staring at her. ‚ÄúWho are you?‚Äù

