Chapter 83: The Bible

The silence of the wilderness was often deafening, broken only by the soft hum of the wind and the distant sounds of nature that filled the air. But there, on the outskirts of the North Sea, Ham and I stood in the middle of a vast and quiet stretch of land, our journey now shaped by something far deeper than we had expected. What began as a search for self-identity and purpose had now shifted into a confrontation with the deepest layers of existence itself. Ham‚Äôs past had emerged like a long-forgotten echo, and with it came questions far more profound than I could have anticipated.

