I had always known that stories shaped our understanding of the world, but I never expected to find myself face to face with the ancient words of The Bible. A collection of stories, history, and lessons that had shaped humanity for millennia. Ham‚Äôs revelations were beginning to pull me into this world‚Äîone that was both familiar and strange. The Bible wasn‚Äôt just a book; it was a lens through which everything could be understood.
