As we continued our journey, the landscape began to change. The fields gave way to forests, thick and dense, as if the land itself was holding onto its secrets. We came across a small, hidden grove‚Äîa peaceful place, untouched by time. There, in the center, was a small wooden structure, weathered by the elements but still standing strong. It looked ancient, as though it had been here long before we arrived.

