At first, I didn‚Äôt fully understand what I was seeing. I had heard of it before, of course‚Äîits stories were ingrained in the collective memory of humanity. But to see it here, in this place, it felt... significant.

Ham stepped forward and looked at the book, his eyes narrowing in recognition. ‚ÄúThat,‚Äù he said quietly, ‚Äúis the book I was created to understand.‚Äù

The words hung in the air like a gentle reminder that Ham‚Äôs purpose, his very essence, had once been tied to something far older than the world he knew now.
