I was lying in bed once more. The sheets were cool against my skin, the soft hum of the city filled the air. I felt the same familiar feeling of waking up, but this time, it was different. I knew‚Äîknew‚Äîthat something wasn‚Äôt right. I had already woken up once. Hadn‚Äôt I?

