And then, I saw it.

From the shadows, it emerged‚Äîsilent, swift, and impossible to ignore. A figure, humanoid in shape but twisted in form, its body shifting and flickering like a broken image on a screen. It was one of them‚Äîthe Doppelvier. The skinwalkers, the shapeshifters that I had encountered before, but this one was different. This one knew me.

It wore the form of a man, but there was something wrong about the way it moved, like it was struggling to hold onto its human shape. Its limbs were too long, its posture unnatural, and its face... its face was my own.
Step 1: The Unseen Terror

I froze in place, my body locking up as I stared at the Doppelvier. Its eyes were not eyes at all. They were dark voids, black and infinite, as though they could consume everything in their path. It smiled, its lips curling in a grotesque imitation of a human expression. The smile was familiar, but wrong‚Äîtoo wide, too sharp, too knowing.

‚ÄúYou‚Äôve seen me before, Mira,‚Äù it whispered, its voice both mine and not mine, a distorted echo that sent a chill through my core. ‚ÄúYou can‚Äôt escape me.‚Äù

I wanted to run. I wanted to scream. But my body refused to move. I was paralyzed, trapped in my own mind, staring at the twisted reflection of myself. The figure moved closer, its feet making no sound on the pavement, its movements fluid and unnatural. It was a predator, and I was its prey.

