Chapter 93: Paranoia

The night had grown colder, and the shadows seemed deeper than they had been before. It was as though the very air in Mirror City had thickened, filled with an unease that hung over everything like a storm waiting to break. The echoes of Aemily‚Äôs words, and the weight of our shared nightmare, still lingered in my mind. I couldn‚Äôt shake the feeling that something was watching, something that had crossed the line between dreams and reality, and was now moving in the spaces between.

