Chapter 96: Poor Deer

I returned to my apartment cautiously, my heart still hammering from the chaos that had just unfolded. The door creaked as I pushed it open, and the first thing I noticed was the silence. The world had slowed, as if holding its breath after the storm that had just passed. The deer was nowhere to be seen. The wreckage of my apartment remained, the shattered window, the overturned furniture, and the scattered debris‚Äîa testament to the frantic energy the poor creature had unleashed in its panic.

