I flinched at the words. Power. Control. Freedom. The temptation was there, gnawing at the edges of my thoughts. The idea of ending the constant struggle, of having the power to shape my own reality‚Äîit was enticing. But I knew better. I had seen what the skinwalkers could do. I had felt the weight of their presence. This wasn‚Äôt freedom. This was imprisonment.

‚ÄúYou think I‚Äôll just... join you?‚Äù I said, my voice steady, though my heart pounded in my chest. ‚ÄúI‚Äôll never be one of you. I‚Äôll never be a part of this.‚Äù

The President‚Äôs grin widened, its dark eyes gleaming with something I couldn‚Äôt quite identify‚Äîanger, amusement, or perhaps something far more dangerous.

‚ÄúWe‚Äôll see,‚Äù it said, its voice carrying an ominous promise. ‚ÄúYou can resist all you want, Mira. But in the end, we all wear the same skin. And sooner or later, you will, too.‚Äù
Step 4: The Choice

I stared back at the President, the weight of its words pressing down on me. The choice was clear. I could fight. I could resist. But it would be hard. The city, the skinwalkers‚Äîeverything about this place was designed to break me down, to twist my reality into something I couldn‚Äôt escape.

But I knew one thing for sure. I wasn‚Äôt going to give in. Not to the fear. Not to the illusions. Not to the President.

